Mumbai, Apr 4 (PTI) Actor Manoj Bajpayee says the credit for his success in the film industry goes to his "so called" flop movies. The actor says he has faced a lot a rejection and the failures have made him what he is. Failures, rejections, they make you the man that you are. I am a living example of an actor making a career out of flops," Bajpayee told PTI. The actor, best known for featuring in critically acclaimed films like "Satya", "Shool" and "Gangs of Wasseypur", says movies which do not work at the box office, are often the ones which have longer shelf life. 